      "MDR1 (ABCB1) gene mutation — less prevalent than Aussies but still present. Genetic test is inexpensive via Washington State University. Affected dogs can have life-threatening reactions to ivermectin (high doses), loperamide, acepromazine. Worth testing every Border Collie.",
