      "Progressive retinal atrophy (PRA) + glaucoma — annual ACVO eye exam catches changes.",
      "Mediastinal lymphoma — over-represented in young Siamese; presents as labored breathing from chest fluid.",
      "Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy (HCM) — present at modest rates; annual echocardiogram from age 5+ is reasonable.",
      "Diabetes mellitus — over-represented in middle-aged Siamese, especially if overweight.",
