      "Reputable BSH breeders run echocardiogram screening + PKD + hemophilia B genetic tests for both parents. Walk away if a breeder can't show recent results.",
      "If your BSH male is scheduled for surgery — even routine neuter — confirm hemophilia B testing first. Affected males bleed dangerously without prep.",
